  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nTruffle migrations cannot currently be written in TypeScript. The only workaround I found is with [TypeChain][1], but the *.ts files need to be transpiled before they are run, so it's not ideal. I could also use [ts-node][2] (as explained in [#717][3]) , but I would prefer not having to fiddle with low-level tools when using Truffle.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTruffle should allow users to write the files under the \"migrations\" directory in TypeScript, parse them and execute them. If a `tsconfig.ts` doesn't exist, Truffle should throw an error and stop the execution.\r\n\r\n[1]: https://github.com/ethereum-ts/TypeChain/tree/master/examples/truffle-v5\r\n[2]: https://www.npmjs.com/package/ts-node\r\n[3]: https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/717",
